description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Division 3 are looking for a clinical educator to join our team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you feel ready to take on a new and exciting role? Are you enthusiastic and passionate about clinical education to ensure our staff are equipped with the skills required to give the very best patient care? Are you adaptable to situations and enjoy enhancing people’s knowledge? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If so this may be the job for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will require you to be involved in the planning and implementation of educational packages in ED in response to the varying needs of the staff based within the speciality across all sites at University Hospitals Birmingham. In doing so you will need to work closely with the wider ED educators and wider divisional/trust education teams to ensure high quality education is delivered and maintained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In addition to the educational requirements of ED, you will also be required to support the wider divisional and trust educational strategies, which at this current time includes fundamental and varying education developed in response to COVID-19. This includes but is not limited to skills educational and pastoral support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be well supported in your new role and you will be equipped with the skills and confidence you require to be an effective clinical educator.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a very exciting time for education and if you feel you would like to be part of the team please feel free to contact me for an informal discussion. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note this post is over multiple sites so cross site cover is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Assessment centre will take place w/c 16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November for those successful at this interview date is 27&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
